body:
@l15k4 Thanks for your catches
1. about the `--updateDescriptor` flag, you're right. I will handle that. 
2. about the loading all of segments, you're right. it loads all of the segments notwithstanding segment versions. It should be improved. But, I think that it would be better to put that improvement in another PR.

@gianm hm, restarts / shutdowns currently use the same logic. 

If the shutdown is a 'final' shutdown, I think there's value in letting running tasks finish and publish. That would allow someone to use shutdown as a way to do an early stop without waiting for taskDuration to elapse - i.e. they spin up a supervisor, pump 1000 messages into it, and then shutdown the supervisor to publish those segments regardless of what taskDuration was set to.

Although maybe your point is more that if some tasks are in a bad state and they don't **all** publish their segments (therefore triggering the shutdown timeout), then having incomplete output is the same or worse than having no output at all and it doesn't matter if we kill the publishing tasks in this case - which I agree with.
